MyReports - Statistic reports for MySQL Servers
===============================================

Description
-----------

This is a personal project realized in Python language and Django v1.3 web
framework. Basically consists in a MySQL variable-value collector and a
customizable report generator for one or more MySQL servers configured.


Installation
------------

1) Get the code from the Github repository:

    ~$ git clone git@github.com:ariel17/myreports.git

2) Create a virtual environment for Python using virtualenv
   [http://www.virtualenv.org/] and virtualenvwrapper
   [http://www.doughellmann.com/projects/virtualenvwrapper/]:

    ~$ mkvirtualenv --no-site-packages --distribute myreports

3) Install dependences and RRDTool [http://oss.oetiker.ch/rrdtool/]:

    (myreports)~/myreports$ pip install -r deploy/requeriments/devel.txt

    (myreports)~/myreports$ sudo apt-get install rrdtool  # debian/ubuntu

5) Configure settings.py using settings.example.py as base file.

6) Adjust your prefered database and sync:

     (myreports)~/myreports$ python manage.py syncdb

7) Run the test server, the collector RPC daemon, the RPC client or the image
   creator:

    (myreports)~/myreports$ python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8080  # /admin/

    (myreports)~/myreports$ python manage.py collector_rpc --port 5000

    (myreports)~/myreports$ python manage.py collector_query --port 5000

    (myreports)~/myreports$ python manage.py collector-graph

    You can always check for --help .


Some day, everything will be easier :)

